# APEX LOGIC — Context Protocol

**Before doing anything**, read these files in order:

1. `APEX_LOGIC_PLAN.md` — master plan, stack, file map, design constraints, build sequence
2. `memory-bank/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` — what is being worked on RIGHT NOW, recent decisions, current blockers
3. `memory-bank/PROGRESS.md` — what is done, what is not started, what is blocked

If you are making ANY code change, also read:
4. `memory-bank/COMPONENT_MAP.md` — to understand what other files your change may break

If you are making a decision (brand, color, font, layout, component behavior):
5. `memory-bank/DECISIONS.md` — to see if this was already decided and what it downstream affects

## Non-Negotiable Design Constraints (from the plan — always enforce)
- `rounded-none` everywhere — no consumer rounded corners
- `tabular-nums` on all numeric columns
- `font-mono` — monospace throughout
- `humanIntent-always-visible` — Human Intent never hidden behind a click
- `terminal-continuous-scroll` — Terminal log animates continuously
- `paused-state-must-pulse` — Amber PAUSED badge uses `animate-pulse`
- `plainenglish-before-diff` — Business risk summary always above code diff
- Aesthetic: **Cyberpunk Bloomberg Terminal** — `bg-neutral-950`, thin borders, no softness

## Stack (never deviate)
- React 19 + Vite
- Tailwind CSS 4
- Lucide React (icons)
- react-countup (animated counters)
- React Context + useState (no backend, no database)

## After completing any task
Update `memory-bank/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` with:
- What you just did
- Any decisions made
- What the next step is
- Any new blockers discovered
